cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques applied to clinical data, which is a common topic in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of rule-based systems is also a common approach in NLP, which makes cs.LG (machine learning) another likely sub-category. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant, as the paper deals with identifying patients who meet certain criteria. Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR) are less likely but still possible sub-categories, as they are also relevant to the healthcare industry.
